All Packages

Package Summary 
Package Description
basics.math
Provides general access to all robot components and basic functions.
basics.math.downhill
Downhill optimization.
basics.math.rot
Mathematical functions for modelling rotations and translations.
basics.math.solids
Geometric computations on 3D solids.
basics.obj
This package provides basic objects, e.g. pair-objects.
basics.util
This package provides utility functions and containers.
kin.dirkin
Direct kinematics computation.
kin.dyn
This package contains dynamic components of the robot's model.
kin.dyn.closed
This package contains dynamic components related to closed-chain kinematics.
kin.env
Virtual environment.
kin.env.geom
2D environment geomtries.
kin.env.obstacles
Obstacles in the virtual environment.
kin.env.obstaclesdyn
Dynamic obstacles in the virtual environment.
kin.env.trigger
Triggers sent by the virtual environment.
kin.execmodels
Simulation's execution models such as manipulators or grippers.
kin.invkin.closed
Inverse kinematics implementations with closed solutions.
kin.invkin.downhill
Inverse kinematics implementations based on downhill optimization.
kin.invkin.jacobian
Inverse kinematics implementations based on Jacobians.
kin.model
This package contains static components of the robot's model.
kin.model.closed
This package contains static components related to closed-chain kinematics.
kin.phy
Physical computation.
kin.render
Rendering the 3D model (native).
kin.render.renderobj
Objects that can be rendered in 3D (native).
kin.renderfx
Rendering the 3D model (JavaFX).
kin.renderfx.renderobj
Objects that can be rendered in 3D (JavaFX).
kin.sim
The simulation.
kin.sim.cmd
Commander facilities of the simulation.
kin.sim.debug
Debug facilities of the simulation.
kin.sim.trid
3D point cloud screen and corresponding functions.
kin.sim.trid.renderobj
Objects that can be rendered in on the 3D point cloud screen.
kin.trigger
Implementation of the trigger system.
manipulators
This package contains example manipulator models.
platform
Classes with platform-dependent meaning – they are different on the real Robot (if it sometimes exists) and simulator.
robotinterface
Provides general access to all robot components and basic functions.
robotinterface.cmd
This package supports commands from the user to the robot controller.
robotinterface.debug
Debugging tools such as print log.
robotinterface.dirkin
Direct kinematics interface.
robotinterface.invkin
Inverse kinematics interface.
robotinterface.manipulator
Provides general access to all manipulator facilities.
robotinterface.motors
Provides general access to robot motors, such as servos and linear motors.
robotinterface.passives
Provides general access to robot passive elements, such as linear passive or axis-rotation passive.
robotinterface.trigger
This package provides trigger services.
